The paper deals with the transmission of analogue source over a fading channel, which is a common topic in information theory (cs.IT) and network communications (cs.NI). The use of buffer to store the quantized analogue source before transmission is a common technique in multimedia systems (cs.MM). The investigation of the tradeoff between distortion and delay is a problem in control systems (cs.SY) and optimization (cs.COM).
